{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859047033,"sessionID":"ses_2868d92eeffeTMhwSkPxfLEkO4","part":{"id":"prt_d797295de001hqDsTKcRTLC2Ow","messageID":"msg_d79728f4c001U2TrRkmFoMU3AM","sessionID":"ses_2868d92eeffeTMhwSkPxfLEkO4","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_7e77984773624cbaab972533","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-024/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-024/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-024 — DockerService 封装\n2: \n3: **Module:** cmd/cli\n4: **Language:** Python\n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ## 目的\n8: \n9: \n10: \n11: ## 范围\n12: \n13: ### 包含\n14: \n15: \n16: \n17: ### 不包含\n18: \n19: \n20: \n21: ## 架构概要\n22: \n23: \n24: \n25: ## 上游依赖\n26: \n27: \n28: \n29: ## 状态\n30: \n31: - [ ] 提案审查\n32: - [ ] 实现\n33: - [ ] 验证\n\n(End of file - total 33 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-024 — DockerService 封装\n\n**Module:** cmd/cli\n**Language:** Python\n**Size:** M\n\n## 目的\n\n\n\n## 范围\n\n### 包含\n\n\n\n### 不包含\n\n\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-024/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775859047014,"end":1775859047031}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859048372,"sessionID":"ses_2868d92eeffeTMhwSkPxfLEkO4","part":{"id":"prt_d79729af1001b2vmkVY721lfuC","messageID":"msg_d79728f4c001U2TrRkmFoMU3AM","sessionID":"ses_2868d92eeffeTMhwSkPxfLEkO4","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_7a30ed5613774bf091580bb3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-024: DockerService 封装 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n6: - **Language:** Python\n7: - **Size:** M\n8: - **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n9: \n10: ## Delta Requirements\n11: \n12: ### Requirement: DockerService initialization\n13: \n14: The system SHALL provide a `DockerService` class that encapsulates Docker SDK operations, initialized with an optional `verbose` flag.\n15: \n16: #### Scenario: Default initialization\n17: - **GIVEN** `DockerService()` is called with no arguments\n18: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n19: - **THEN** `self.verbose` SHALL be `False` and a Docker client SHALL be initialized via `docker.from_env()`\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Verbose initialization\n22: - **GIVEN** `DockerService(verbose=True)` is called\n23: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n24: - **THEN** `self.verbose` SHALL be `True` and the logger SHALL be configured for debug-level output\n25: \n26: ### Requirement: Docker availability check\n27: \n28: The system SHALL verify that the Docker daemon is running and reachable before attempting build or push operations.\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Docker is available\n31: - **GIVEN** the Docker daemon is running and accessible\n32: - **WHEN** `DockerService.check_docker_available()` is called\n33: - **THEN** it SHALL return `True`\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Docker is unavailable\n36: - **GIVEN** the Docker daemon is not running or the SDK cannot connect\n37: - **WHEN** `DockerService.check_docker_available()` is called\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL catch `docker.errors.DockerException` (or connection errors) and return `False`\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: Build image\n41: \n42: The system SHALL build a Docker image from a Dockerfile and context path, with optional build arguments and a configurable tag.\n43: \n44: #### Scenario: Build with default tag\n45: - **GIVEN** a valid `dockerfile_path` and `context_path`\n46: - **WHEN** `build_image(dockerfile_path, context_path, \"my-agent\")` is called\n47: - **THEN** it SHALL build the image tagged `my-agent:latest` and return a dict with keys `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`\n48: \n49: #### Scenario: Build with custom tag\n50: - **GIVEN** a valid workspace\n51: - **WHEN** `build_image(..., image_name=\"my-agent\", tag=\"v1.2.3\")` is called\n52: - **THEN** the image SHALL be tagged `my-agent:v1.2.3`\n53: \n54: #### Scenario: Build with build arguments\n55: - **GIVEN** `build_args={\"PIP_INDEX_URL\": \"https://proxy.example.com/simple\"}` is passed\n56: - **WHEN** `build_image` is called\n57: - **THEN** the Docker build SHALL receive `buildargs` containing the provided key-value pairs\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Build failure\n60: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile contains a syntax error or a build step fails\n61: - **WHEN** `build_image` is called\n62: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `RuntimeError` with a message describing the build failure\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: Build records elapsed time\n65: - **GIVEN** a build is initiated\n66: - **WHEN** `build_image` completes successfully\n67: - **THEN** the returned dict SHALL include `build_time` as a formatted duration string (e.g., `\"12.34s\"`)\n68: \n69: ### Requirement: Image info retrieval\n70: \n71: The system SHALL retrieve metadata about a local Docker image, including its ID and human-readable size.\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: Image exists locally\n74: - **GIVEN** an image `my-agent:latest` exists in the local Docker daemon\n75: - **WHEN** `get_image_info(\"my-agent:latest\")` is called\n76: - **THEN** it SHALL return a dict with keys `image_id` and `image_size` (human-readable, e.g., `\"256.5 MB\"`)\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: Image does not exist\n79: - **GIVEN** no image named `nonexistent:latest` exists locally\n80: - **WHEN** `get_image_info(\"nonexistent:latest\")` is called\n81: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` with a message indicating the image was not found\n82: \n83: ### Requirement: Size formatting\n84: \n85: The system SHALL convert byte counts to human-readable size strings.\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: Bytes\n88: - **GIVEN** a size of `512` bytes\n89: - **WHEN** `_format_size(512)` is called\n90: - **THEN** it SHALL return `\"512 B\"`\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Megabytes\n93: - **GIVEN** a size of `1048576` bytes (1 MiB)\n94: - **WHEN** `_format_size(1048576)` is called\n95: - **THEN** it SHALL return `\"1.0 MB\"`\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Gigabytes\n98: - **GIVEN** a size of `1073741824` bytes (1 GiB)\n99: - **WHEN** `_format_size(1073741824)` is called\n100: - **THEN** it SHALL return `\"1.0 GB\"`\n101: \n102: ### Requirement: Push image\n103: \n104: The system SHALL push a local Docker image to a registry, optionally authenticating and retagging.\n105: \n106: #### Scenario: Push without registry URL\n107: - **GIVEN** a local image `my-agent:v1.0.0` exists\n108: - **WHEN** `push_image(\"my-agent:v1.0.0\")` is called with no `registry_url`\n109: - **THEN** it SHALL push the image to its existing tag and return a dict with `pushed_image` and `push_time`\n110: \n111: #### Scenario: Push with registry URL and credentials\n112: - **GIVEN** `registry_url=\"registry.example.com\"`, `username`, and `password` are provided\n113: - **WHEN** `push_image(\"my-agent:v1.0.0\", registry_url, username, password)` is called\n114: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n115:   1. Login to the registry via `_docker_login_sdk`\n116:   2. Retag the image to `{registry_url}/my-agent:v1.0.0` via `_tag_image_sdk`\n117:   3. Push the retagged image\n118:   4. Return `pushed_image` as the full registry-prefixed tag\n119: \n120: #### Scenario: Push without credentials\n121: - **GIVEN** `registry_url` is provided but `username` or `password` is `None`\n122: - **WHEN** `push_image` is called\n123: - **THEN** it SHALL skip the login step and attempt to push using existing Docker credentials\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: Push failure\n126: - **GIVEN** the registry is unreachable or authentication fails\n127: - **WHEN** `push_image` is called\n128: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `RuntimeError` with a message describing the push failure\n129: \n130: #### Scenario: Push records elapsed time\n131: - **GIVEN** a push is initiated\n132: - **WHEN** `push_image` completes successfully\n133: - **THEN** the returned dict SHALL include `push_time` as a formatted duration string\n134: \n135: ### Requirement: Docker login\n136: \n137: The system SHALL authenticate to a Docker registry using the Docker SDK.\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: Successful login\n140: - **GIVEN** valid `registry`, `username`, and `password`\n141: - **WHEN** `_docker_login_sdk(registry, username, password)` is called\n142: - **THEN** it SHALL call `client.login()` with the provided credentials and succeed without raising\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: Login failure\n145: - **GIVEN** invalid credentials or unreachable registry\n146: - **WHEN** `_docker_login_sdk` is called\n147: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `RuntimeError` with the login error message\n148: \n149: ### Requirement: Image tagging\n150: \n151: The system SHALL retag a local Docker image.\n152: \n153: #### Scenario: Successful tag\n154: - **GIVEN** source image `my-agent:v1.0.0` exists\n155: - **WHEN** `_tag_image_sdk(\"my-agent:v1.0.0\", \"registry.example.com/my-agent:v1.0.0\")` is called\n156: - **THEN** the target tag SHALL exist in the local Docker daemon\n157: \n158: #### Scenario: Tag failure\n159: - **GIVEN** the source image does not exist\n160: - **WHEN** `_tag_image_sdk` is called\n161: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `RuntimeError` with the tagging error message\n162: \n163: ### Requirement: Remove image\n164: \n165: The system SHALL remove a local Docker image and handle failures gracefully.\n166: \n167: #### Scenario: Successful removal\n168: - **GIVEN** image `my-agent:old` exists locally\n169: - **WHEN** `remove_image(\"my-agent:old\")` is called\n170: - **THEN** it SHALL return `True` and the image SHALL no longer be listed locally\n171: \n172: #### Scenario: Removal failure\n173: - **GIVEN** image `my-agent:in-use` is referenced by a running container or does not exist\n174: - **WHEN** `remove_image(\"my-agent:in-use\")` is called\n175: - **THEN** it SHALL log a warning and return `False`\n176: \n177: ### Requirement: Verbose logging during operations\n178: \n179: The system SHALL emit detailed logs during Docker operations when `verbose=True`.\n180: \n181: #### Scenario: Verbose build logging\n182: - **GIVEN** `DockerService(verbose=True)`\n183: - **WHEN** `build_image` is called\n184: - **THEN** it SHALL log the Dockerfile path, context path, image name, tag, and any build arguments\n185: \n186: #### Scenario: Verbose push logging\n187: - **GIVEN** `DockerService(verbose=True)`\n188: - **WHEN** `push_image` is called with credentials\n189: - **THEN** it SHALL log the registry URL, username (not password), and target image name\n190: \n191: ## File changes\n192: \n193: | Action | File | Description |\n194: |--------|------|-------------|\n195: | Add | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | DockerService class with build, push, info, remove operations |\n196: | Add | `tests/services/test_docker_service.py` | DockerService unit tests |\n\n(End of file - total 196 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-024: DockerService 封装 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: DockerService initialization\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `DockerService` class that encapsulates Docker SDK operations, initialized with an optional `verbose` flag.\n\n#### Scenario: Default initialization\n- **GIVEN** `DockerService()` is called with no arguments\n- **WHEN** the instance is created\n- **THEN** `self.verbose` SHALL be `False` and a Docker client SHALL be initialized via `docker.from_env()`\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775859048362,"end":1775859048370}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859049665,"sessionID":"ses_2868d92eeffeTMhwSkPxfLEkO4","part":{"id":"prt_d7972a043001WqPxZJNcqF5FFd","messageID":"msg_d79728f4c001U2TrRkmFoMU3AM","sessionID":"ses_2868d92eeffeTMhwSkPxfLEkO4","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_3c20d97b90d3460b996cfda8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-024/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-024/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-024 — DockerService 封装 — Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: `DockerService` (`agentcube/services/docker_service.py`) 是 AgentCube CLI 的 Docker 守护进程交互层，封装 `docker` SDK for Python（`docker>=6.0.0`），提供镜像构建、推送、登录、打标、信息查询和清理能力。它被 `BuildRuntime`（本地 Docker 构建）和 `PublishRuntime`（本地镜像推送至 Registry）直接调用。\n6: \n7: **Scope**: 补全 spec 中定义但当前实现缺失的方法（`get_image_info`、`_get_image_info`、`remove_image`），修正与 spec 不一致的签名（`push_image`、`_docker_login_sdk`、`_tag_image_sdk` 的返回值类型），并完善错误处理。\n8: \n9: **Size**: M — 约 60 行新增代码 + 签名调整 + 测试覆盖。\n10: \n11: ---\n12: \n13: ## Architecture\n14: \n15: ```\n16: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n17: │                     CLI Commands                         │\n18: │  pack │ build │ publish │ invoke │ status               │\n19: └──────────┬──────────────────────────┬────────────────────┘\n20:            │                          │\n21:     ┌──────▼──────┐            ┌──────▼──────┐\n22:     │BuildRuntime │            │PublishRuntime│\n23:     └──────┬──────┘            └──────┬──────┘\n24:            │                          │\n25:            │  check_docker_available()│\n26:            │  build_image()           │  check_docker_available()\n27:            │                          │  _docker_login_sdk()\n28:            │                          │  push_image()\n29:            └──────────┬───────────────┘\n30:                       │\n31:               ┌───────▼───────┐\n32:               │ DockerService │\n33:               │               │\n34:               │ docker.from_  │\n35:               │    env()      │\n36:               └───────┬───────┘\n37:                       │\n38:               ┌───────▼───────┐\n39:               │  Docker SDK   │\n40:               │  (docker-py)  │\n41:               └───────────────┘\n42: ```\n43: \n44: **Design principles**:\n45: - 每次方法调用独立创建 `docker.from_env()` 客户端（无状态、线程安全、避免长连接泄漏）\n46: - 所有公共方法返回 `Dict[str, Any]` 或 `bool`，异常向上传播由 Runtime 层捕获\n47: - `_` 前缀方法为内部辅助，不供外部直接调用\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ## Component Design\n52: \n53: ### `DockerService.__init__(verbose: bool = False)`\n54: \n55: 存储 `verbose` 标志，用于后续可选的详细日志输出（当前实现中 verbose 未主动使用，保留接口以匹配其他 Service 的一致性）。\n56: \n57: ### `check_docker_available() -> bool`\n58: \n59: 通过 `docker.from_env()` 创建客户端并调用 `client.ping()`。任何异常（连接失败、权限不足、守护进程未运行）返回 `False`。\n60: \n61: **Current**: ✅ 已实现，符合 spec。\n62: \n63: ### `build_image(dockerfile_path, context_path, image_name, tag, build_args) -> Dict[str, str]`\n64: \n65: 调用 `client.images.build()` 执行构建，返回包含 `image_name`、`image_id`（short_id）、`image_size`（人类可读格式）、`build_time`（秒数，保留两位小数）的字典。\n66: \n67: `build_args` 用于传递代理设置（如 `HTTP_PROXY`/`HTTPS_PROXY`），直接透传给 Docker SDK 的 `buildargs` 参数。\n68: \n69: **Current**: ✅ 已实现，符合 spec。\n70: \n71: ### `get_image_info(image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]`\n72: \n73: 获取本地镜像的元信息。公共方法，内部委托给 `_get_image_info`。\n74: \n75: 返回字典包含：\n76: - `image_id`: 完整 SHA256 ID\n77: - `short_id`: 截短的 ID（`sha256:xxxxx`）\n78: - `size`: 人类可读大小（如 `50.0 MB`）\n79: - `tags`: 镜像关联的标签列表\n80: - `created`: 创建时间字符串\n81: \n82: **Current**: ❌ 缺失，需新增。\n83: \n84: ### `_get_image_info(image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]`\n85: \n86: 内部实现：通过 `client.images.get(image_name)` 获取 `Image` 对象，从 `attrs` 中提取元数据并格式化。\n87: \n88: **Current**: ❌ 缺失，需新增。\n89: \n90: ### `_format_size(size_bytes: int) -> str`\n91: \n92: 将字节数格式化为人类可读字符串。阈值：`<1024` → `B`，`<1MB` → `KB`，`<1GB` → `MB`，`>=1GB` → `GB`。\n93: \n94: **Current**: ✅ 已实现，符合 spec。\n95: \n96: ### `push_image(image_name, registry_url, username, password) -> Dict[str, str]`\n97: \n98: 将本地镜像推送至 Registry。\n99: \n100: **Spec 签名**（与当前实现不同）:\n101: ```python\n102: def push_image(\n103:     self,\n104:     image_name: str,\n105:     registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n106:     username: Optional[str] = None,\n107:     password: Optional[str] = None,\n108: ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n109: ```\n110: \n111: **当前签名**:\n112: ```python\n113: def push_image(\n114:     self,\n115:     image_tag: str,          # 完整标签如 registry.example.com/my-agent:v1.0.0\n116:     registry_url: str,       # 必填\n117:     username: Optional[str] = None,\n118:     password: Optional[str] = None,\n119: ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n120: ```\n121: \n122: **需要调整**: 将 `push_image` 签名改为 spec 定义的 `image_name` + 可选 `registry_url`，内部逻辑：\n123: 1. 如果提供 `registry_url`，先调用 `_tag_image_sdk` 将 `image_name` 打目标标签\n124: 2. 如果提供 `username` 和 `password`，调用 `_docker_login_sdk` 登录\n125: 3. 调用 `client.images.push()` 推送，流式处理日志（当前未消费 push 返回值中的流式日志）\n126: 4. 返回 `{\"pushed_image\": <full_tag>, \"push_time\": \"<n.nn>s\"}`（spec 要求返回 `pushed_image` 和 `push_time`）\n127: \n128: **Current**: ⚠️ 已实现但签名与 spec 不一致，返回值缺少 `push_time`。\n129: \n130: ### `_docker_login_sdk(registry, username, password) -> None`\n131: \n132: 通过 `client.login()` 登录 Registry。\n133: \n134: **Spec 返回值**: `None`\n135: **当前返回值**: `bool`（返回 `True`）\n136: \n137: **需要调整**: 返回值改为 `None`，失败时让 `docker.errors.APIError` 向上传播。\n138: \n139: **Current**: ⚠️ 已实现但返回值类型与 spec 不一致。\n140: \n141: ### `_tag_image_sdk(source_image, target_image) -> None`\n142: \n143: 将本地镜像从 `source_image` 打标为 `target_image`。\n144: \n145: **Spec 返回值**: `None`\n146: **当前返回值**: `bool`（返回 `True`）\n147: \n148: **需要调整**: 返回值改为 `None`。\n149: \n150: **Current**: ⚠️ 已实现但返回值类型与 spec 不一致。\n151: \n152: ### `remove_image(image_name: str) -> bool`\n153: \n154: 删除本地 Docker 镜像。成功返回 `True`；失败时记录 warning 日志并返回 `False`。\n155: \n156: 使用 `client.images.remove(image_name)` 执行删除。捕获 `docker.errors.ImageNotFound` 和 `docker.errors.APIError`，记录 warning 后返回 `False`。\n157: \n158: **Current**: ❌ 缺失，需新增。\n159: \n160: ---\n161: \n162: ## Data Flow Details\n163: \n164: ### Build 流程\n165: \n166: ```\n167: BuildRuntime._build_local()\n168:   ├── DockerService.check_docker_available()  → bool\n169:   └── DockerService.build_image()\n170:         ├── docker.from_env()\n171:         ├── client.images.build(path, dockerfile, tag, buildargs)\n172:         ├── client.images.get(image.id)       → 获取 Size\n173:         └── return {image_name, image_id, image_size, build_time}\n174: ```\n175: \n176: ### Publish 流程（local build mode）\n177: \n178: ```\n179: PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image()\n180:   ├── DockerService.check_docker_available()  → bool\n181:   ├── DockerService._docker_login_sdk()       → None (if credentials)\n182:   └── DockerService.push_image()\n183:         ├── docker.from_env()\n184:         ├── client.images.push(repository, tag, auth_config)\n185:         └── return {pushed_image, push_time}\n186: ```\n187: \n188: ---\n189: \n190: ## Error Handling\n191: \n192: | 场景 | 异常类型 | 处理方式 |\n193: |------|----------|----------|\n194: | Docker 守护进程不可达 | `docker.errors.DockerException` | `check_docker_available()` 返回 `False`；其他方法向上传播 |\n195: | 镜像不存在 | `docker.errors.ImageNotFound` | `remove_image()` 返回 `False` + warning；其他方法向上传播 |\n196: | 构建失败 | `docker.errors.BuildError` | 向上传播，由 `BuildRuntime` / CLI `_handle_error` 捕获 |\n197: | Registry 认证失败 | `docker.errors.APIError` | `_docker_login_sdk()` 向上传播；`push_image()` 向上传播 |\n198: | 推送失败 | `docker.errors.APIError` | 向上传播，由 `PublishRuntime` / CLI 捕获 |\n199: | 权限不足 | `docker.errors.APIError` (403) | 向上传播 |\n200: \n201: **关键约束**: `DockerService` 本身不打印错误信息或调用 `sys.exit()` — 所有异常向上传播，由 Runtime 层或 CLI `_handle_error` 统一处理。\n202: \n203: ---\n204: \n205: ## Testing Strategy\n206: \n207: ### 现有测试覆盖（`tests/services/test_docker_service.py`）\n208: \n209: | 测试类 | 覆盖方法 | 状态 |\n210: |--------|----------|------|\n211: | `TestDockerServiceCheckDockerAvailableRunning` | `check_docker_available` (success) | ✅ |\n212: | `TestDockerServiceCheckDockerAvailableNotRunning` | `check_docker_available` (failure) | ✅ |\n213: | `TestDockerServiceBuildImageSuccess` | `build_image` (success) | ✅ |\n214: | `TestDockerServiceBuildImageWithProxy` | `build_image` (with buildargs) | ✅ |\n215: | `TestDockerServiceBuildImageFailure` | `build_image` (error propagation) | ✅ |\n216: | `TestDockerServiceFormatSize*` | `_format_size` (B/KB/MB/GB) | ✅ |\n217: | `TestDockerService_PushImage_Success` | `push_image` (success) | ⚠️ 需更新断言 |\n218: | `TestDockerService_PushImage_WithCredentials` | `push_image` (auth) | ⚠️ 需更新断言 |\n219: | `TestDockerService_PushImage_Failure` | `push_image` (APIError) | ⚠️ 需更新断言 |\n220: | `TestDockerService_DockerLoginSdk_Success` | `_docker_login_sdk` (success) | ⚠️ 需更新断言 |\n221: | `TestDockerService_DockerLoginSdk_Failure` | `_docker_login_sdk` (APIError) | ⚠️ 需更新断言 |\n222: | `TestDockerService_TagImageSdk_Success` | `_tag_image_sdk` (success) | ⚠️ 需更新断言 |\n223: \n224: ### 需新增测试\n225: \n226: | 测试类 | 覆盖方法 | 场景 |\n227: |--------|----------|------|\n228: | `TestDockerServiceGetImageInfo` | `get_image_info` | 存在镜像，返回完整元信息 |\n229: | `TestDockerServiceGetImageInfo` | `get_image_info` | 镜像不存在，抛出 `ImageNotFound` |\n230: | `TestDockerServiceGetImageInfo` | `_get_image_info` | 内部实现验证 |\n231: | `TestDockerServiceRemoveImage` | `remove_image` | 成功删除返回 `True` |\n232: | `TestDockerServiceRemoveImage` | `remove_image` | 镜像不存在返回 `False` + warning |\n233: | `TestDockerServiceRemoveImage` | `remove_image` | API 错误返回 `False` + warning |\n234: | `TestDockerServicePushImageSpec` | `push_image` | 新签名：`image_name` + `registry_url` |\n235: | `TestDockerServicePushImageSpec` | `push_image` | 无 `registry_url` 时直接推送本地标签 |\n236: | `TestDockerServicePushImageSpec` | `push_image` | 返回 `push_time` |\n237: \n238: ### Mock 策略\n239: \n240: 所有测试通过 `patch(\"agentcube.services.docker_service.docker.from_env\")` 模拟 Docker 客户端，不依赖真实 Docker 守护进程。\n241: \n242: ---\n243: \n244: ## Implementation Notes\n245: \n246: ### 签名变更影响分析\n247: \n248: `push_image` 签名变更会影响以下调用方：\n249: \n250: 1. **`PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image()`** (`publish_runtime.py:105`):\n251:    ```python\n252:    # Before:\n253:    result = docker_service.push_image(image_tag, registry_url or \"\", username, password)\n254:    # After:\n255:    result = docker_service.push_image(image_tag, registry_url or \"\", username, password)\n256:    ```\n257:    调用方传递的第一个参数是完整 `image_tag`（如 `registry.example.com/my-agent:v1.0.0`），在新签名中作为 `image_name` 使用。如果 `registry_url` 为空字符串，不进行重新打标，直接推送。行为兼容。\n258: \n259: 2. **测试文件** (`test_docker_service.py`): 需更新断言以匹配新返回值（`push_time` 替代 `status`）。\n260: \n261: ### 返回值类型变更\n262: \n263: `_docker_login_sdk` 和 `_tag_image_sdk` 的返回值从 `bool` 改为 `None`。由于它们是 `_` 前缀的内部方法，且调用方不检查返回值（`publish_runtime.py:103` 调用 `_docker_login_sdk` 但未使用返回值），此变更为安全。\n264: \n265: ### 缺失方法实现要点\n266: \n267: **`get_image_info` / `_get_image_info`**:\n268: ```python\n269: def _get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]:\n270:     client = docker.from_env()\n271:     image = client.images.get(image_name)\n272:     attrs = image.attrs\n273:     return {\n274:         \"image_id\": image.id,\n275:         \"short_id\": image.short_id,\n276:         \"size\": self._format_size(int(attrs.get(\"Size\", 0) or 0)),\n277:         \"tags\": \", \".join(image.tags) if image.tags else \"<none>\",\n278:         \"created\": attrs.get(\"Created\", \"unknown\"),\n279:     }\n280: \n281: def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]:\n282:     return self._get_image_info(image_name)\n283: ```\n284: \n285: **`remove_image`**:\n286: ```python\n287: def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool:\n288:     import logging\n289:     logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n290:     try:\n291:         client = docker.from_env()\n292:         client.images.remove(image_name)\n293:         return True\n294:     except (docker.errors.ImageNotFound, docker.errors.APIError) as e:\n295:         logger.warning(\"Failed to remove image %s: %s\", image_name, e)\n296:         return False\n297: ```\n298: \n299: **`push_image` 签名调整**:\n300: ```python\n301: def push_image(\n302:     self,\n303:     image_name: str,\n304:     registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n305:     username: Optional[str] = None,\n306:     password: Optional[str] = None,\n307: ) -> Dict[str, str]:\n308:     import time\n309:     client = docker.from_env()\n310:     start_time = time.time()\n311: \n312:     if registry_url:\n313:         # Determine target tag\n314:         parts = image_name.rsplit(\":\", 1)\n315:         repo = parts[0]\n316:         tag = parts[1] if len(parts) > 1 else \"latest\"\n317:         target = f\"{registry_url}/{repo}:{tag}\"\n318:         self._tag_image_sdk(image_name, target)\n319:         push_repo = f\"{registry_url}/{repo}\"\n320:         push_tag = tag\n321:     else:\n322:         parts = image_name.rsplit(\":\", 1)\n323:         push_repo = parts[0]\n324:         push_tag = parts[1] if len(parts) > 1 else \"latest\"\n325: \n326:     auth_config = None\n327:     if username and password:\n328:         auth_config = {\"username\": username, \"password\": password}\n329:         self._docker_login_sdk(registry_url, username, password)\n330: \n331:     client.images.push(push_repo, tag=push_tag, auth_config=auth_config)\n332:     push_time = time.time() - start_time\n333:     return {\"pushed_image\": image_name, \"push_time\": f\"{push_time:.2f}s\"}\n334: ```\n\n(End of file - total 334 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-024 — DockerService 封装 — Design\n\n## Overview\n\n`DockerService` (`agentcube/services/docker_service.py`) 是 AgentCube CLI 的 Docker 守护进程交互层，封装 `docker` SDK for Python（`docker>=6.0.0`），提供镜像构建、推送、登录、打标、信息查询和清理能力。它被 `BuildRuntime`（本地 Docker 构建）和 `PublishRuntime`（本地镜像推送至 Registry）直接调用。\n\n**Scope**: 补全 spec 中定义但当前实现缺失的方法（`get_image_info`、`_get_image_info`、`remove_image`），修正与 spec 不一致的签名（`push_image`、`_docker_login_sdk`、`_tag_image_sdk` 的返回值类型），并完善错误处理。\n\n**Size**: M — 约 60 行新增代码 + 签名调整 + 测试覆盖。\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     CLI Commands                         │\n│  pack │ build │ publish │ invoke │ status               │\n└──────────┬──────────────────────────┬────────────────────┘\n           │                          │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-024/design.md","time":{"start":1775859049656,"end":1775859049663}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859051036,"sessionID":"ses_2868d92eeffeTMhwSkPxfLEkO4","part":{"id":"prt_d7972a590001VkGnA6KUodD7Vv","messageID":"msg_d79728f4c001U2TrRkmFoMU3AM","sessionID":"ses_2868d92eeffeTMhwSkPxfLEkO4","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_28be5e76aaba4c9b844b4a2d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-024/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-024/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-024 — DockerService 封装 — Tasks\n2: \n3: > **Module:** cmd/cli\n4: > **Language:** Python\n5: > **Size:** M\n6: > **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n7: > **Reference:** `changes/AR-024/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-024/design.md`, `changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md`\n8: > **Dependency:** None\n9: \n10: ## T1. Fix `_docker_login_sdk` return type: `bool` → `None`\n11: \n12: - [ ] Change `_docker_login_sdk` return type annotation from `-> bool` to `-> None`\n13: - [ ] Remove `return True` statement; let `client.login()` result fall through\n14: - [ ] Update docstring to reflect `None` return\n15: - [ ] Write test: successful login returns `None` (no exception raised)\n16: - [ ] Write test: login failure raises `docker.errors.APIError` (propagates upward)\n17: \n18: **Verification:** `pytest tests/services/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerService_DockerLoginSdk_Success -v` passes with `None` assertion\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## T2. Fix `_tag_image_sdk` return type: `bool` → `None`\n23: \n24: - [ ] Change `_tag_image_sdk` return type annotation from `-> bool` to `-> None`\n25: - [ ] Remove `return True` statement; let `image.tag()` result fall through\n26: - [ ] Update docstring to reflect `None` return\n27: - [ ] Write test: successful tagging returns `None` (no exception raised)\n28: - [ ] Write test: tagging failure (source image not found) raises `docker.errors.ImageNotFound`\n29: \n30: **Verification:** `pytest tests/services/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerService_TagImageSdk_Success -v` passes with `None` assertion\n31: \n32: ---\n33: \n34: ## T3. Implement `_get_image_info` (internal helper)\n35: \n36: - [ ] Add `_get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]` method\n37: - [ ] Create `docker.from_env()` client inside method\n38: - [ ] Call `client.images.get(image_name)` to retrieve `Image` object\n39: - [ ] Extract `image_id` (full ID), `short_id`, `size` (via `_format_size`), `tags` (comma-joined or `\"<none>\"`), `created` from `image.attrs`\n40: - [ ] Return dict with keys: `image_id`, `short_id`, `size`, `tags`, `created`\n41: - [ ] Write test: image exists → returns dict with all five keys populated correctly\n42: - [ ] Write test: image not found → `docker.errors.ImageNotFound` propagates upward\n43: \n44: **Verification:** `pytest tests/services/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerServiceGetImageInfo -v` passes\n45: \n46: ---\n47: \n48: ## T4. Implement `get_image_info` (public method)\n49: \n50: - [ ] Add `get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]` method\n51: - [ ] Delegate to `self._get_image_info(image_name)`\n52: - [ ] Write test: delegates to `_get_image_info` and returns result\n53: - [ ] Write test: image not found → `ValueError` with descriptive message (per delta-spec)\n54: \n55: **Verification:** `pytest tests/services/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerServiceGetImageInfo -v` passes; public method wraps internal correctly\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ## T5. Implement `remove_image`\n60: \n61: - [ ] Add `remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool` method\n62: - [ ] Create `docker.from_env()` client inside method\n63: - [ ] Call `client.images.remove(image_name)`; return `True` on success\n64: - [ ] Catch `docker.errors.ImageNotFound` → log warning, return `False`\n65: - [ ] Catch `docker.errors.APIError` → log warning, return `False`\n66: - [ ] Write test: image exists → returns `True`, `client.images.remove` called once\n67: - [ ] Write test: image not found → returns `False`, warning logged\n68: - [ ] Write test: API error (e.g., image in use) → returns `False`, warning logged\n69: \n70: **Verification:** `pytest tests/services/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerServiceRemoveImage -v` passes\n71: \n72: ---\n73: \n74: ## T6. Fix `push_image` signature and implementation\n75: \n76: - [ ] Change first parameter from `image_tag: str` to `image_name: str`\n77: - [ ] Change `registry_url: str` to `registry_url: Optional[str] = None`\n78: - [ ] Add `import time` (if not already present at top of method)\n79: - [ ] Record `start_time = time.time()` at method entry\n80: - [ ] If `registry_url` is provided:\n81:   - Parse `image_name` to extract repo and tag\n82:   - Build target tag: `{registry_url}/{repo}:{tag}`\n83:   - Call `self._tag_image_sdk(image_name, target)`\n84:   - Set `push_repo` and `push_tag` from target\n85: - [ ] If `registry_url` is not provided:\n86:   - Parse `image_name` to extract repo and tag\n87:   - Set `push_repo` and `push_tag` directly\n88: - [ ] If `username` and `password` provided, call `self._docker_login_sdk(registry_url, username, password)`\n89: - [ ] Call `client.images.push(push_repo, tag=push_tag, auth_config=...)`\n90: - [ ] Compute `push_time = time.time() - start_time`\n91: - [ ] Return `{\"pushed_image\": image_name, \"push_time\": f\"{push_time:.2f}s\"}`\n92: - [ ] Update docstring to match new signature and return value\n93: - [ ] Write test: push without `registry_url` → pushes directly, returns `pushed_image` + `push_time`\n94: - [ ] Write test: push with `registry_url` and credentials → tags, logs in, pushes, returns full tag\n95: - [ ] Write test: push with `registry_url` but no credentials → skips login, pushes\n96: - [ ] Write test: push failure → `docker.errors.APIError` propagates upward\n97: \n98: **Verification:** `pytest tests/services/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerServicePushImageSpec -v` passes\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ## T7. Update `PublishRuntime` caller for new `push_image` signature\n103: \n104: - [ ] Read `publish_runtime.py` to identify `push_image` call site(s)\n105: - [ ] Update call to match new signature: `push_image(image_name, registry_url, username, password)`\n106: - [ ] Verify caller does not depend on old return keys (`status` → now `push_time`)\n107: - [ ] Write test: `PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image()` works with new `push_image` signature (mocked `DockerService`)\n108: \n109: **Verification:** `pytest tests/runtime/test_publish_runtime.py -v` passes; no `TypeError` from signature mismatch\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ## T8. Update existing tests for signature/return changes\n114: \n115: - [ ] Update `TestDockerService_PushImage_Success` assertions: expect `push_time` key instead of `status`\n116: - [ ] Update `TestDockerService_PushImage_WithCredentials` assertions: match new signature and return\n117: - [ ] Update `TestDockerService_PushImage_Failure` assertions: verify `APIError` propagation\n118: - [ ] Update `TestDockerService_DockerLoginSdk_Success` assertion: expect `None` return instead of `True`\n119: - [ ] Update `TestDockerService_DockerLoginSdk_Failure` assertion: verify `APIError` propagation\n120: - [ ] Update `TestDockerService_TagImageSdk_Success` assertion: expect `None` return instead of `True`\n121: \n122: **Verification:** All existing `test_docker_service.py` tests pass with updated assertions\n123: \n124: ---\n125: \n126: ## T9. Lint, type-check, coverage gate\n127: \n128: - [ ] `ruff check cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py` — no violations\n129: - [ ] `ruff check cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` — no violations\n130: - [ ] `mypy cmd/cli/agentcube/` — no type errors\n131: - [ ] `pytest tests/services/test_docker_service.py -v` — all pass\n132: - [ ] `pytest tests/runtime/test_publish_runtime.py -v` — all pass\n133: - [ ] `pytest tests/ --cov=agentcube.services.docker_service --cov-report=term-missing` — coverage ≥ 90%\n134: \n135: **Verification:** All lint/type-check/test commands pass with zero errors\n136: \n137: ---\n138: \n139: ## Task Dependencies\n140: \n141: ```\n142: T1 ──┐\n143: T2 ──┼── T6 ── T7 ── T9\n144:      │           │\n145: T3 ──┤           │\n146: T4 ──┤           │\n147: T5 ──┤           │\n148:      │           │\n149: T8 ──┴───────────┘\n150: ```\n151: \n152: ## Parallelizable Groups\n153: \n154: | Group | Tasks | Prerequisites |\n155: |-------|-------|---------------|\n156: | G1 | T1, T2, T3, T5 | None (independent method changes) |\n157: | G2 | T4 | T3 |\n158: | G3 | T6 | T1, T2 |\n159: | G4 | T7, T8 | T6 |\n160: | G5 | T9 | T4, T5, T7, T8 |\n161: \n162: ---\n163: \n164: ## Acceptance Criteria\n165: \n166: | # | Criterion | Command |\n167: |---|-----------|---------|\n168: | AC1 | `get_image_info` returns dict with `image_id`, `short_id`, `size`, `tags`, `created` | `pytest tests/...::TestDockerServiceGetImageInfo -v` |\n169: | AC2 | `remove_image` returns `True` on success, `False` + warning on failure | `pytest tests/...::TestDockerServiceRemoveImage -v` |\n170: | AC3 | `push_image` accepts `image_name` + optional `registry_url`, returns `pushed_image` + `push_time` | `pytest tests/...::TestDockerServicePushImageSpec -v` |\n171: | AC4 | `_docker_login_sdk` returns `None` (not `bool`) | `pytest tests/...::TestDockerService_DockerLoginSdk_Success -v` |\n172: | AC5 | `_tag_image_sdk` returns `None` (not `bool`) | `pytest tests/...::TestDockerService_TagImageSdk_Success -v` |\n173: | AC6 | `PublishRuntime` caller updated and functional | `pytest tests/runtime/test_publish_runtime.py -v` |\n174: | AC7 | All existing tests pass with updated assertions | `pytest tests/services/test_docker_service.py -v` |\n175: | AC8 | Lint and type-check pass | `ruff check` + `mypy` with zero violations |\n176: | AC9 | Test coverage ≥ 90% for `docker_service.py` | `pytest --cov=agentcube.services.docker_service` |\n\n(End of file - total 176 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-024 — DockerService 封装 — Tasks\n\n> **Module:** cmd/cli\n> **Language:** Python\n> **Size:** M\n> **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n> **Reference:** `changes/AR-024/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-024/design.md`, `changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md`\n> **Dependency:** None\n\n## T1. Fix `_docker_login_sdk` return type: `bool` → `None`\n\n- [ ] Change `_docker_login_sdk` return type annotation from `-> bool` to `-> None`\n- [ ] Remove `return True` statement; let `client.login()` result fall through\n- [ ] Update docstring to reflect `None` return\n- [ ] Write test: successful login returns `None` (no exception raised)\n- [ ] Write test: login failure raises `docker.errors.APIError` (propagates upward)\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/services/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerService_DockerLoginSdk_Success -v` passes with `None` assertion\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-024/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775859051029,"end":1775859051035}}}}
